Based on the billiard balls and cue sticks in the background. as well as the design on the  vest, and the time-line,  this is likely John  <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9807E5D9163BE533A25755C2A9609C946095D6CF" rel="nofollow">G.</a> Horgan, also referred to as John <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9D06E3D8103BE633A25756C2A9639C946296D6CF" rel="nofollow">C.</a> Horgan.

<b>John G. Horgan</b> (1871 ? - 1921)  world's champion three-cushion billiard player in 1912, and the world's pocket billiard champion in 1906. --Excerpted<i> <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9807E5D9163BE533A25755C2A9609C946095D6CF" rel="nofollow">New York Times</a></i>
